<paragraph blockId="17.[138,1185,966,1086]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735">
This species was reported as a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[679,750,966,990]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735">China</collectingCountry>
from Sechuan Province and 
<collectingRegion country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beasley CW &amp; Kaczmarek L &amp; Michalczyk L" box="[254,478,998,1022]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735" pagination="3 - 10" refId="ref5616" refString="Beasley CW, Kaczmarek L, Michalczyk L. 2006. New records of tardigrades from China, with zoogeographical remarks. Biological Letters 43: 3 - 10." type="journal article" year="2006">Beasley et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
). My specimens fit the description of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramazzotti G &amp; Maucci W" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735" pagination="1 - 1012" refId="ref6561" refString="Ramazzotti G, Maucci W. 1983. Il Phylum Tardigrada. 3 rd ed. Memorie dell'Isituto Italiano di Idrobiologia 41: 1 - 1012. (CW Beasley, Eng translation)." type="journal article" year="1983">Ramazzotti and Maucci 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dastych H" box="[360,524,1030,1054]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735" pagination="1 - 288" refId="ref5898" refString="Dastych H. 1988. The Tardigrada of Poland. Monografie Fauny Polski 16: 1 - 288." type="journal article" year="1988">Dastych 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="McInnes SJ" box="[537,710,1030,1054]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735" pagination="1419 - 1445" refId="ref6334" refString="McInnes SJ. 1995. Tardigrades from Signy Island, South Orkney Islands, with particular reference to freshwater species. Journal of Natural History 29: 1419 - 1445." type="journal article" year="1995">McInnes 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pilato G &amp; Binda MG" box="[723,988,1030,1054]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2735" pagination="181 - 185" refId="ref6421" refString="Pilato G, Binda MG. 1997 / 98. A comparison of Diphascon (D.) alpinum Murray, 1906, D. (D.) chilenense Plate, 1889 and D. (D.) pingue Marcus, 1936 (Tardigrada), and description of a new species. Zoologischer Anzeiger 236: 181 - 185." type="journal article" year="1997">Pilato and Binda 1997</bibRefCitation>
/98). It has never been reported from the Tsinling Mountains.
</paragraph>
